<para>
  Select all the &sgmts; on the internal boundaries of the &skel;.
  Internal boundaries separate &elems; that have different dominant
  <link linkend="Section-Concepts-PixelCategory">pixel
  categories</link>.  That is, the dominant pixel types within the
  &elems; have different assigned &materials; or belong to different
  <link linkend="Section-Concepts-Microstructure-Pixel_Group">pixel
  groups</link>.
</para>
<para>
  Note that the resulting &sgmt; selection does not include segments
  that are on the exterior of the &micro;.
</para>

<figure id="Figure-boundary_segments">
  <title>Selecting Internal Boundary Segments</title>
  <mediaobject>
    <imageobject>
	  <imagedata fileref="FIGURES/skel_selection/segs_internal_boundary.png"
                 format="PNG" contentwidth="315px"/>
    </imageobject>
    <caption>
	  <para>
	    The pixels in this &micro; have been grouped by <link
	    linkend="MenuItem-OOF.Image.AutoGroup">color</link>, and the
	    &sgmts; in green have been selected because they lie between
	    &elems; that are dominated by different pixel groups.
	  </para>
    </caption>
  </mediaobject>
</figure>

